00:00:10.812 --> 00:00:13.213 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] 30 minutes
since I accepted the game.

00:00:13.347 --> 00:00:14.682 position:30% line:89% align:start
While not long,

00:00:14.816 --> 00:00:16.283 position:21% line:83% align:start
it's been time enough
to call someone over,

00:00:16.416 --> 00:00:17.652 position:13% line:83% align:start
and to secure my connection
with Kagaya

00:00:17.785 --> 00:00:19.052 position:16% line:89% align:start
against nasty surprises.

00:00:19.186 --> 00:00:21.623 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[phone ringing]
-Hm?

00:00:25.860 --> 00:00:27.896 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>Yoo-hoo! Can you see me?</i>

00:00:28.228 --> 00:00:29.831 position:27% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] The game
Akizuki challenged me to

00:00:29.964 --> 00:00:31.431 position:13% line:89% align:start
is Tabletop Treasure Hunt.

00:00:31.566 --> 00:00:33.066 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
 <i>It's your cute friend, Noa.</i>

00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:35.168 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>Did you miss me?</i> [giggles]

00:00:35.302 --> 00:00:37.271 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
I can't win. I can't lose.

00:00:37.404 --> 00:00:39.941 position:19% line:83% align:start
And this time, a draw's
clearly not in the cards.

00:00:40.474 --> 00:00:42.142 position:7% line:89% align:start
I've been backed into a corner.

00:00:42.710 --> 00:00:45.212 position:10% line:83% align:start
What's worse is I don't even
understand the rules.

00:00:45.345 --> 00:00:47.281 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>Oh? Ignoring me, huh?</i>

00:00:47.414 --> 00:00:48.550 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>Well, have it your way.</i>

00:00:48.683 --> 00:00:50.484 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'll ask a "Question" then.</i>

00:00:50.618 --> 00:00:53.353 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Is your partner hiding somewhere</i>
 <i>on or below the third floor?</i>

00:00:53.487 --> 00:00:54.488 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
A question?

00:00:54.989 --> 00:00:57.659 position:16% line:83% align:start
[scoffs] <i>Yeah, you know,</i>
 <i>Hiro, a question.</i>

00:00:57.792 --> 00:00:59.861 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>It's a command</i>
 <i>you can use once per turn.</i>

00:00:59.994 --> 00:01:02.997 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>You get to ask your opponent</i>
 <i>a simple yes-or-no question.</i>

00:01:03.130 --> 00:01:05.098 position:30% line:83% align:start
Word of advice,
you better not lie.

00:01:05.232 --> 00:01:07.902 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's an instant forfeit,
so be honest.

00:01:08.036 --> 00:01:09.336 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
In that case,

00:01:09.469 --> 00:01:11.238 position:27% line:83% align:start
since my partner
isn't on any of those floors,

00:01:11.371 --> 00:01:12.707 position:27% line:89% align:start
the answer is no.

00:01:12.840 --> 00:01:13.975 position:44% line:89% align:start
Okay!

00:01:14.107 --> 00:01:15.777 position:24% line:83% align:start
Then, now we enter
the "Move" phase.

00:01:15.910 --> 00:01:18.211 position:19% line:83% align:start
This is another command
you can use once every turn.

00:01:18.345 --> 00:01:20.748 position:27% line:83% align:start
It lets you move
up to three spaces.

00:01:21.081 --> 00:01:22.316 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Spaces?

00:01:22.617 --> 00:01:23.785 position:41% line:89% align:start
I see.

00:01:23.918 --> 00:01:26.119 position:10% line:83% align:start
So each room in the building
counts as a space.

00:01:26.253 --> 00:01:27.655 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
 <i>You can change floors</i>

00:01:27.789 --> 00:01:29.222 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>by taking the stairs</i>
 <i>on either side, too.</i>

00:01:29.991 --> 00:01:32.827 position:7% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] So, Akizuki and I are
in the hall by Home Economics,

00:01:32.961 --> 00:01:34.896 position:13% line:83% align:start
and our respective partners
have been concealed

00:01:35.029 --> 00:01:36.396 position:13% line:89% align:start
in rooms unbeknownst to us.

00:01:36.531 --> 00:01:38.600 position:13% line:83% align:start
What's more, each room has
an electronic lock,

00:01:38.733 --> 00:01:40.969 position:7% line:83% align:start
requiring some kind of command
to open.

00:01:41.101 --> 00:01:43.170 position:10% line:89% align:start
Because, of course, they do.

00:01:43.303 --> 00:01:44.639 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
Since you're new to this,

00:01:44.772 --> 00:01:46.574 position:13% line:83% align:start
I think I'll go easy on you
just this once.

00:01:46.708 --> 00:01:48.810 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll move one space
over to the right,

00:01:48.943 --> 00:01:50.177 position:19% line:89% align:start
and end my turn there.

00:01:50.310 --> 00:01:51.779 position:33% line:89% align:start
Okay, I'm up.

00:01:51.913 --> 00:01:53.681 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
You seriously fell for that?

00:01:53.815 --> 00:01:55.248 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[Noa giggles]
-[HIROTO] Huh?

00:01:55.382 --> 00:01:57.417 position:7% line:83% align:start
Sorry. Girls and their secrets,
you know?

00:01:57.919 --> 00:01:59.921 position:27% line:83% align:start
My first ability
is actually "Double Action",

00:02:00.054 --> 00:02:02.557 position:19% line:83% align:start
which allows me to take
two whole turns in a row.

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:04.191 position:10% line:83% align:start
-So here's another question.
-[phone pings]

00:02:04.324 --> 00:02:06.159 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>Is your partner</i>
 <i>instead hiding somewhere</i>

00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:07.795 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>on or above the fifth floor?</i>

00:02:08.295 --> 00:02:10.330 position:10% line:83% align:start
What kind of ass-pull ability
is that?

00:02:10.464 --> 00:02:12.533 position:44% line:83% align:start
Hey,
this is totally on the level.

00:02:12.667 --> 00:02:14.936 position:30% line:83% align:start
I just tweaked
a couple conditions is all.

00:02:15.069 --> 00:02:16.738 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Uh. No.

00:02:16.871 --> 00:02:18.305 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
Hurray.

00:02:18.438 --> 00:02:19.841 position:24% line:83% align:start
Now I know she's up
on the fourth floor, don't I?

00:02:19.974 --> 00:02:21.709 position:41% line:83% align:start
I think
I'll shuffle one space right

00:02:21.843 --> 00:02:22.810 position:27% line:89% align:start
and call it good.

00:02:23.544 --> 00:02:25.479 position:5% line:83% align:start
I really want to see you squirm,
Hiroto,

00:02:25.613 --> 00:02:28.215 position:16% line:83% align:start
so I'm going to take this
nice and slow.

00:02:28.348 --> 00:02:29.483 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:02:30.350 --> 00:02:31.485 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroto sighs]

00:02:32.386 --> 00:02:33.688 position:30% line:89% align:start
[horn blaring]

00:02:33.821 --> 00:02:35.188 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh, that's right.

00:02:39.661 --> 00:02:40.762 position:44% line:89% align:start
Good.

00:02:41.896 --> 00:02:43.097 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>Hey, it's me.</i>

00:02:43.497 --> 00:02:44.599 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Hiroto chuckles]

00:02:44.732 --> 00:02:46.299 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Looking fly, Saionji.</i>

00:02:46.433 --> 00:02:48.703 position:7% line:89% align:start
[laughs] Perfect disguise, huh?

00:02:49.103 --> 00:02:50.303 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Thanks for this.

00:02:50.437 --> 00:02:51.939 position:7% line:89% align:start
If you hadn't come to help out,

00:02:52.073 --> 00:02:54.509 position:10% line:83% align:start
this game would've been over
before I even accepted it.

00:02:54.642 --> 00:02:56.410 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hey, it's no big deal.

00:02:56.544 --> 00:02:59.113 position:13% line:83% align:start
After all, if you go down,
I go down with you.

00:02:59.246 --> 00:03:00.748 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Hope you're comfy.

00:03:00.882 --> 00:03:02.416 position:13% line:83% align:start
I think you're going to be
locked in there for a while.

00:03:02.550 --> 00:03:04.217 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>That's fine by me.</i>

00:03:04.351 --> 00:03:06.688 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>But I certainly wouldn't say no</i>
 <i>to a little more wiggle room,</i>

00:03:06.821 --> 00:03:08.422 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>or a nice warm cozy blanket.</i>

00:03:08.556 --> 00:03:10.490 position:30% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Yeah,
these cold April nights, huh?

00:03:10.625 --> 00:03:12.426 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sorry, try to hang in there.

00:03:12.560 --> 00:03:14.629 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'll be fine,
just hurry up and win this.

00:03:14.762 --> 00:03:16.531 position:13% line:83% align:start
Let's get Yuki out of here,
quick.

00:03:16.664 --> 00:03:18.800 position:41% line:83% align:start
Right,
then let's recap the rules.

00:03:18.933 --> 00:03:20.267 position:16% line:83% align:start
To win, you have to find
the "treasure"

00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:22.170 position:24% line:83% align:start
that's been hidden
by your opponent.

00:03:22.904 --> 00:03:24.304 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
 <i>The "treasure" is your partner.</i>

00:03:24.438 --> 00:03:26.406 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>So naturally for you, that's me,</i>

00:03:26.541 --> 00:03:28.543 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>and for the Devil Girl,</i>
 <i>it's Yuki.</i>

00:03:28.676 --> 00:03:29.944 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
The field of play for this game

00:03:30.078 --> 00:03:31.311 position:10% line:89% align:start
is Eimei's largest building.

00:03:31.445 --> 00:03:32.345 position:35% line:89% align:start
Building A.

00:03:33.181 --> 00:03:35.049 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] <i>Spaces correspond</i>
 <i>to rooms on each floor,</i>

00:03:35.183 --> 00:03:37.985 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>as represented</i>
 <i>by this six-by-eight grid map.</i>

00:03:38.119 --> 00:03:40.655 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>There are four commands</i>
 <i>you can use during your turn.</i>

00:03:40.788 --> 00:03:43.290 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>The first two are the ones</i>
 <i>the Devil Girl showed off.</i>

00:03:43.423 --> 00:03:45.193 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>"Question" and "Move".</i>

00:03:45.325 --> 00:03:46.861 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
The third is "Answer",

00:03:46.994 --> 00:03:49.063 position:13% line:83% align:start
which you use when you know
where the opponent's partner is.

00:03:49.197 --> 00:03:51.833 position:16% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] <i>If you're right,</i>
 <i>the game ends then and there.</i>

00:03:51.966 --> 00:03:53.701 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
But, in order to use "Answer",

00:03:53.835 --> 00:03:56.269 position:10% line:83% align:start
the player has to be standing
in front of the classroom.

00:03:56.403 --> 00:03:58.673 position:27% line:83% align:start
Also, each player
has three Answer Points.

00:03:58.806 --> 00:04:00.541 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
 <i>Which, of course,</i>

00:04:00.675 --> 00:04:02.342 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>means you can only afford</i>
 <i>to get it wrong twice.</i>

00:04:02.476 --> 00:04:04.377 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>"Retreat"</i>
 <i>is the tricky one of the bunch.</i>

00:04:04.512 --> 00:04:07.915 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>It's the command that lets you</i>
 <i>move your partner around freely.</i>

00:04:08.381 --> 00:04:09.217 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yeah.

00:04:09.349 --> 00:04:10.551 position:16% line:89% align:start
It resets their position,

00:04:10.685 --> 00:04:12.252 position:16% line:83% align:start
allowing them to relocate
to a new space

00:04:12.385 --> 00:04:13.654 position:21% line:89% align:start
on the playing grid.

00:04:13.788 --> 00:04:15.857 position:27% line:83% align:start
But, it burns up
one Answer Point to use it.

00:04:16.423 --> 00:04:18.559 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] <i>So basically,</i>
 <i>those three Answer Points</i>

00:04:18.693 --> 00:04:21.562 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>are the currency of both</i>
 <i>your offense and defense.</i>

00:04:21.696 --> 00:04:22.997 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Speaking of defense,

00:04:23.131 --> 00:04:24.732 position:16% line:83% align:start
you can move your partner
even if they're located,

00:04:24.866 --> 00:04:27.969 position:21% line:83% align:start
but if you do, that's
another Answer Point gone.

00:04:28.102 --> 00:04:29.469 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
It's no wonder

00:04:29.604 --> 00:04:31.371 position:13% line:83% align:start
the Little Devil activated
Double Action on us.

00:04:31.506 --> 00:04:32.874 position:10% line:89% align:start
Getting to go twice as fast?

00:04:33.007 --> 00:04:34.776 position:27% line:83% align:start
That's a big edge
in a game like this.

00:04:34.909 --> 00:04:37.578 position:24% line:83% align:start
She can pressure me
into using my answers up.

00:04:37.712 --> 00:04:39.781 position:19% line:83% align:start
Make me waste them all
trying to protect myself.

00:04:39.914 --> 00:04:41.649 position:10% line:83% align:start
That "Double Action" ability
of hers

00:04:41.783 --> 00:04:44.317 position:16% line:83% align:start
-is way too overpowered!
-[SARASA] <i>Yeah.</i>

00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:46.053 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>I bet it's some illegal exploit</i>
 <i>she got</i>

00:04:46.187 --> 00:04:47.454 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>from the guy behind the curtain.</i>

00:04:47.588 --> 00:04:48.756 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Wonderful,

00:04:48.890 --> 00:04:49.991 position:30% line:83% align:start
probably means
her other abilities

00:04:50.124 --> 00:04:51.092 position:13% line:89% align:start
are going to suck as well.

00:04:51.391 --> 00:04:52.794 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>All right, then.</i>

00:04:52.927 --> 00:04:54.327 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I think that about does it</i>
 <i>for the rules,</i>

00:04:54.461 --> 00:04:56.264 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>so what's the strategy here?</i>

00:04:56.396 --> 00:04:57.799 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>If you win this one,</i>

00:04:57.932 --> 00:04:59.634 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>then Yuki will have to leave</i>
 <i>the island,</i>

00:04:59.767 --> 00:05:01.736 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>but if you lose,</i>
 <i>it's bye-bye Shinohara.</i>

00:05:01.869 --> 00:05:04.572 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>A tricky situation,</i>
 <i>but I'm resourceful.</i>

00:05:04.705 --> 00:05:06.473 position:27% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] [gasps]
Wait, does that mean you--

00:05:06.607 --> 00:05:08.142 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>It's not 100% yet.</i>

00:05:08.276 --> 00:05:11.478 position:10% line:83% align:start
[exhales] It first struck me
in your game with Kugasaki,

00:05:11.612 --> 00:05:13.313 position:24% line:83% align:start
but you're actually
a bona fide genius

00:05:13.446 --> 00:05:14.549 position:33% line:83% align:start
when it comes
to thinking up plans

00:05:14.682 --> 00:05:16.150 position:13% line:89% align:start
under pressure, aren't you?

00:05:16.284 --> 00:05:17.484 position:24% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh. Thank you.

00:05:18.119 --> 00:05:19.520 position:21% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] <i>But you know</i>
 <i>you're never going to win</i>

00:05:19.654 --> 00:05:20.655 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>if you play fair.</i>

00:05:20.788 --> 00:05:21.956 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Not against the Devil Girl.</i>

00:05:22.089 --> 00:05:23.925 position:44% line:83% align:start
Then,
let it be an eye for an eye

00:05:24.058 --> 00:05:25.560 position:16% line:89% align:start
and a cheat for a cheat.

00:05:25.860 --> 00:05:28.029 position:21% line:83% align:start
Think you can beat us
at playing dirty, do you?

00:05:28.596 --> 00:05:30.363 position:10% line:89% align:start
You're going to regret that.

00:05:31.199 --> 00:05:32.867 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:34.735 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Player 2's first turn.

00:05:34.869 --> 00:05:36.604 position:10% line:89% align:start
I posed a question to Akizuki

00:05:36.737 --> 00:05:39.273 position:10% line:83% align:start
and worked out that Himeji's
on the third floor or below.

00:05:39.406 --> 00:05:41.309 position:13% line:89% align:start
Then, I moved three spaces.

00:05:42.210 --> 00:05:43.578 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[horn blaring]
-[HIROTO] After that,

00:05:43.711 --> 00:05:45.580 position:33% line:83% align:start
Akizuki took
her second real turn.

00:05:45.713 --> 00:05:47.447 position:30% line:89% align:start
[phone pinging]

00:05:47.582 --> 00:05:49.083 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
With her Double Action,

00:05:49.217 --> 00:05:52.119 position:7% line:83% align:start
she narrowed Saionji's position
down to one of two spots,

00:05:52.253 --> 00:05:53.855 position:13% line:89% align:start
But only moved two spaces.

00:05:54.622 --> 00:05:56.691 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
 <i>Bye-bye now, Hiroto!</i>

00:05:56.824 --> 00:05:58.960 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] All right,
here goes turn number two.

00:05:59.093 --> 00:06:00.294 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[phone ringing]
Hm?

00:06:00.427 --> 00:06:01.696 position:27% line:89% align:start
Kagaya. We good?

00:06:01.829 --> 00:06:03.396 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
 <i>Nah, it ain't happening.</i>

00:06:03.531 --> 00:06:04.665 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>Noa's been a real killjoy</i>

00:06:04.799 --> 00:06:06.300 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>and used</i>
 <i>the Area Barrier ability</i>

00:06:06.433 --> 00:06:07.535 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>on the whole school.</i>

00:06:07.668 --> 00:06:08.803 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
[groans] Really?

00:06:08.936 --> 00:06:10.671 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
 <i>Mm, but you know,</i>

00:06:10.805 --> 00:06:12.573 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>there is that Device sensor</i>
 <i>program I wrote for you</i>

00:06:12.707 --> 00:06:14.208 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>at the start</i>
 <i>of the Elimination Battle.</i>

00:06:14.342 --> 00:06:15.676 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yeah. Of course.

00:06:15.810 --> 00:06:17.111 position:7% line:83% align:start
Since there's no other students
around,

00:06:17.245 --> 00:06:19.412 position:30% line:83% align:start
I could use it
to find Himeji, easily!

00:06:19.547 --> 00:06:21.148 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
 <i>Actually, no, sorry.</i>

00:06:21.282 --> 00:06:23.517 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>You'd need to connect</i>
 <i>to an outside server for that.</i>

00:06:23.651 --> 00:06:25.219 position:44% line:83% align:start
 <i>Man,</i>
 <i>this anti-interference thing</i>

00:06:25.353 --> 00:06:26.419 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>is killing me.</i>

00:06:26.554 --> 00:06:27.855 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Hiroto groans]

00:06:28.222 --> 00:06:30.925 position:13% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] But Area Barrier's
an external defense ability.

00:06:31.058 --> 00:06:33.426 position:13% line:83% align:start
So we can still use cheats
inside it, right?

00:06:33.561 --> 00:06:35.062 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
 <i>Yeah, totes!</i>

00:06:35.196 --> 00:06:37.765 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Though Academy Island's devices</i>
 <i>are pretty high-spec.</i>

00:06:37.899 --> 00:06:39.466 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>You'd need a serious brainiac</i>

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:41.302 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>other than your bespectacled</i>
 <i>big sis there with you</i>

00:06:41.434 --> 00:06:42.637 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>to modify one locally.</i>

00:06:42.770 --> 00:06:43.938 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
It's possible then.

00:06:44.071 --> 00:06:45.640 position:27% line:83% align:start
You think someone
as smart as Akizuki

00:06:45.773 --> 00:06:47.742 position:30% line:83% align:start
could pull off
some tech-tampering like that?

00:06:47.875 --> 00:06:49.110 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
 <i>Maybe.</i>

00:06:49.243 --> 00:06:50.811 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>The specs</i>
 <i>for the modded programs</i>

00:06:50.945 --> 00:06:52.412 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>are living rent-free</i>
 <i>in my grey matter,</i>

00:06:52.546 --> 00:06:53.881 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>but without an operator</i>
 <i>to give them to,</i>

00:06:54.015 --> 00:06:55.683 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>they're not going to do us</i>
 <i>much good.</i>

00:06:56.150 --> 00:06:57.351 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
True.

00:06:57.484 --> 00:06:59.153 position:5% line:83% align:start
But you're forgetting one thing,
Kagaya.

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:02.390 position:16% line:83% align:start
I happen to have a genius
beyond even Akizuki's level

00:07:02.523 --> 00:07:03.624 position:38% line:89% align:start
with me.

00:07:04.158 --> 00:07:05.092 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:07:06.527 --> 00:07:07.828 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[phone pings]
-[Sarasa sighs]

00:07:07.962 --> 00:07:09.764 position:33% line:83% align:start
Second floor,
fourth space from the right.

00:07:09.897 --> 00:07:12.300 position:21% line:83% align:start
That's the classroom
she's been hiding Yuki in.

00:07:12.432 --> 00:07:13.935 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
 <i>Hoodie Girl for the win!</i>

00:07:14.068 --> 00:07:16.304 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>24-hour job in ten minutes!</i>

00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:18.471 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Chills, man. Literal chills!</i>

00:07:18.606 --> 00:07:20.508 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>Ah, just let me be you, girl!</i>

00:07:20.641 --> 00:07:21.809 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Thank you! Thank you!</i>

00:07:21.943 --> 00:07:23.744 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
Time's almost up, Hiroto.

00:07:23.878 --> 00:07:25.813 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm getting kind of tired
waiting here.

00:07:25.947 --> 00:07:28.316 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Okay, then, Akizuki,</i>
 <i>here's a question.</i>

00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:29.817 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh, how exciting.

00:07:29.951 --> 00:07:32.452 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>The room you hid Himeji in is...</i>

00:07:33.554 --> 00:07:35.122 position:21% line:89% align:start
Classroom 1-K, right?

00:07:35.256 --> 00:07:36.657 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-[phone pings]

00:07:37.959 --> 00:07:39.427 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
That would be a "yes".

00:07:39.560 --> 00:07:42.430 position:33% line:83% align:start
Hey, Hiroto,
are you cheating again?

00:07:42.563 --> 00:07:43.864 position:16% line:89% align:start
Now how could I do that?

00:07:43.998 --> 00:07:45.633 position:21% line:83% align:start
I got all tangled up
in your trap

00:07:45.766 --> 00:07:47.802 position:19% line:83% align:start
without even the mercy
of a single decent ability,

00:07:47.935 --> 00:07:50.137 position:35% line:83% align:start
-didn't I?
 <i>-Yeah! But still!</i>

00:07:50.271 --> 00:07:51.505 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Time to move.

00:07:51.639 --> 00:07:52.740 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, look,

00:07:52.873 --> 00:07:54.709 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm only two spots away
from 1-K.

00:07:54.842 --> 00:07:56.544 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's like basically check.

00:07:56.677 --> 00:07:58.312 position:5% line:89% align:start
Your degeneracy knows no bounds,

00:07:58.446 --> 00:07:59.847 position:38% line:83% align:start
-does it?
-[horn blares]

00:07:59.981 --> 00:08:01.916 position:10% line:83% align:start
[NOA] Guess I'll have to stop
going easy on you.

00:08:02.049 --> 00:08:03.250 position:30% line:89% align:start
Question time.

00:08:03.384 --> 00:08:07.455 position:19% line:83% align:start
You're partner's hiding
in Classroom 2-I, yeah?

00:08:07.588 --> 00:08:09.557 position:16% line:89% align:start
Well? She's there, right?

00:08:09.690 --> 00:08:11.058 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>[sighs] Yes.</i>

00:08:11.192 --> 00:08:12.526 position:35% line:89% align:start
There, see?

00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:14.562 position:10% line:83% align:start
You're not the only one who's
good at guessing, are you?

00:08:14.695 --> 00:08:16.797 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I'll move six spaces
in one go.

00:08:17.298 --> 00:08:19.867 position:38% line:83% align:start
[grunts]
She instantly turned it around.

00:08:20.234 --> 00:08:22.370 position:19% line:83% align:start
[NOA] Next, I'll use up
one of my Answer Points

00:08:22.503 --> 00:08:24.672 position:10% line:83% align:start
to make our glum maid friend
move her frilly butt

00:08:24.805 --> 00:08:26.073 position:21% line:89% align:start
to a different room.

00:08:26.207 --> 00:08:28.142 position:24% line:89% align:start
Boo-hoo, so close.

00:08:28.275 --> 00:08:29.276 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:08:30.177 --> 00:08:34.315 position:7% line:83% align:start
Ah! Shinohara, we've just lost
Yuki's Device signal.

00:08:34.448 --> 00:08:35.616 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.118 position:19% line:83% align:start
She probably suspected
we were cheating

00:08:37.251 --> 00:08:38.185 position:24% line:89% align:start
and blocked it out.

00:08:38.719 --> 00:08:39.987 position:13% line:89% align:start
But it made Akizuki use up

00:08:40.121 --> 00:08:42.289 position:19% line:83% align:start
one of her precious few
Answer Points.

00:08:42.423 --> 00:08:43.891 position:10% line:89% align:start
Not a bad outcome in my book.

00:08:44.025 --> 00:08:45.826 position:7% line:83% align:start
-[SHIRAYUKI] Master Shinohara?
-Ah?

00:08:47.361 --> 00:08:48.496 position:24% line:89% align:start
Please forgive me.

00:08:48.863 --> 00:08:50.131 position:13% line:89% align:start
As I'm sure you've noticed,

00:08:50.264 --> 00:08:52.433 position:19% line:83% align:start
I had to cut off access
to my Device.

00:08:52.566 --> 00:08:54.535 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, kind of figured as much.

00:08:54.668 --> 00:08:56.037 position:5% line:89% align:start
Is it okay for us to be talking?

00:08:56.170 --> 00:08:58.005 position:27% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] Yes,
so long as I'm not revealing

00:08:58.139 --> 00:09:00.541 position:16% line:83% align:start
anything disadvantageous
to Miss Akizuki,

00:09:00.674 --> 00:09:01.742 position:27% line:89% align:start
it's permissible.

00:09:02.543 --> 00:09:04.945 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Well, I guess you do
have to move around on foot,

00:09:05.079 --> 00:09:06.047 position:35% line:89% align:start
after all.

00:09:06.180 --> 00:09:07.648 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
It would be convenient

00:09:07.782 --> 00:09:09.250 position:19% line:83% align:start
if I could simply warp
from room to room.

00:09:09.383 --> 00:09:10.718 position:27% line:89% align:start
But, as I can't,

00:09:10.851 --> 00:09:12.553 position:30% line:83% align:start
I've been given
a frustratingly convoluted route

00:09:12.686 --> 00:09:13.888 position:27% line:89% align:start
to throw you off.

00:09:14.021 --> 00:09:15.990 position:38% line:83% align:start
Traipsing
up and down all these stairs,

00:09:16.123 --> 00:09:17.258 position:27% line:89% align:start
it's tiring work.

00:09:17.658 --> 00:09:19.860 position:10% line:83% align:start
Just try not to push yourself
too hard.

00:09:21.262 --> 00:09:22.730 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ah...

00:09:22.863 --> 00:09:25.499 position:7% line:83% align:start
Forecast says it's going to get
real cold tonight after 10 p.m.

00:09:25.633 --> 00:09:26.767 position:35% line:83% align:start
Might want
to keep the room warm,

00:09:26.901 --> 00:09:28.503 position:13% line:89% align:start
so you don't catch a cold.

00:09:28.636 --> 00:09:30.271 position:5% line:89% align:start
That's very considerate, Master.

00:09:30.404 --> 00:09:31.605 position:35% line:89% align:start
Thank you.

00:09:32.106 --> 00:09:33.140 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:09:33.808 --> 00:09:35.976 position:13% line:89% align:start
Excuse me, I must be going.

00:09:40.114 --> 00:09:41.582 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Already past 8:00, huh?

00:09:41.916 --> 00:09:43.284 position:10% line:89% align:start
Himeji's not done moving yet,

00:09:43.417 --> 00:09:46.053 position:21% line:83% align:start
which means Akizuki's
still on her third turn,

00:09:46.187 --> 00:09:48.355 position:10% line:83% align:start
so I guess we're going to be
stuck on hold a while.

00:09:48.856 --> 00:09:50.591 position:21% line:83% align:start
The Devil Girl's lost
one Answer Point,

00:09:50.724 --> 00:09:52.059 position:10% line:89% align:start
but she's still got two left.

00:09:52.193 --> 00:09:54.028 position:7% line:89% align:start
We just lost our Device sensor,

00:09:54.161 --> 00:09:56.597 position:7% line:83% align:start
and we can't rely on questions
to narrow it down.

00:09:56.730 --> 00:09:58.232 position:10% line:89% align:start
It'd take way too much time.

00:09:58.699 --> 00:09:59.534 position:33% line:89% align:start
Yeah, right.

00:09:59.667 --> 00:10:01.001 position:16% line:89% align:start
In a situation like this,

00:10:01.135 --> 00:10:02.870 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'd normally bank on outwitting
my opponent

00:10:03.003 --> 00:10:05.005 position:5% line:89% align:start
with misdirection and deduction.

00:10:05.540 --> 00:10:07.208 position:5% line:89% align:start
Any reason we can't do that now?

00:10:07.341 --> 00:10:09.243 position:19% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] <i>Akizuki's seen</i>
 <i>through every play I've made</i>

00:10:09.376 --> 00:10:11.946 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>since the All-Campus</i>
 <i>Elimination Battle started.</i>

00:10:12.079 --> 00:10:13.781 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>It's the Green Star's effect.</i>

00:10:13.914 --> 00:10:15.449 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>Predict Movement.</i>

00:10:15.584 --> 00:10:17.118 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
With her skills,

00:10:17.251 --> 00:10:19.554 position:7% line:83% align:start
if the Little Devil got a hold
of an ability like that...

00:10:19.687 --> 00:10:21.422 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yeah, it's not good.

00:10:21.556 --> 00:10:22.591 position:13% line:89% align:start
With her level of insight,

00:10:22.723 --> 00:10:24.358 position:16% line:83% align:start
she's practically reading
my mind.

00:10:24.492 --> 00:10:27.428 position:19% line:83% align:start
Although, she has made
two kind of crucial mistakes.

00:10:27.562 --> 00:10:28.362 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Mistakes?

00:10:28.496 --> 00:10:29.730 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:10:29.864 --> 00:10:31.699 position:16% line:83% align:start
The first was in my Trial
against Himeji,

00:10:31.832 --> 00:10:33.767 position:30% line:83% align:start
and the second
actually happened just now,

00:10:33.901 --> 00:10:36.303 position:24% line:83% align:start
with you being able
to pinpoint her location.

00:10:36.437 --> 00:10:37.838 position:33% line:89% align:start
You're right.

00:10:37.972 --> 00:10:38.906 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] I'm trying
to figure out what was different

00:10:39.039 --> 00:10:40.808 position:5% line:89% align:start
about those ploys in particular.

00:10:41.242 --> 00:10:43.878 position:21% line:83% align:start
Someone else's ideas
were mixed in with them.

00:10:44.011 --> 00:10:46.280 position:10% line:83% align:start
-They weren't my plans alone.
-[SARASA] So what?

00:10:46.413 --> 00:10:47.882 position:38% line:83% align:start
You think
the Little Devil's restricted

00:10:48.015 --> 00:10:49.518 position:7% line:83% align:start
to only reading your thoughts,
Shinohara?

00:10:49.650 --> 00:10:52.486 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm saying that if she is,
then it's something to use.

00:10:52.621 --> 00:10:54.488 position:24% line:83% align:start
I mean, it follows
that she'd place Himeji

00:10:54.623 --> 00:10:57.291 position:19% line:83% align:start
somewhere she believes
I wouldn't think to look,

00:10:57.424 --> 00:10:58.726 position:35% line:89% align:start
but then...

00:10:58.859 --> 00:11:00.961 position:33% line:83% align:start
She's failing
to account for what I think.

00:11:02.363 --> 00:11:03.497 position:33% line:89% align:start
[horn blares]

00:11:04.131 --> 00:11:06.400 position:21% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] After moving
to the fourth floor,

00:11:06.535 --> 00:11:07.868 position:19% line:89% align:start
I activated "Retreat".

00:11:08.402 --> 00:11:11.238 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm using up an Answer Point
to move my partner.

00:11:13.974 --> 00:11:15.242 position:19% line:89% align:start
And now, a "Question".

00:11:15.376 --> 00:11:19.813 position:38% line:83% align:start
Is Himeji
in Classrooms 3-E, 3-J, or 3-L?

00:11:20.515 --> 00:11:21.382 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
Yes.

00:11:21.782 --> 00:11:23.751 position:5% line:89% align:start
But there's no way. How'd you...

00:11:23.884 --> 00:11:25.386 position:30% line:89% align:start
How'd you know?

00:11:25.853 --> 00:11:26.954 position:7% line:89% align:start
I fixed it so there couldn't be

00:11:27.087 --> 00:11:28.889 position:16% line:83% align:start
any outside interference
or tricks.

00:11:29.023 --> 00:11:31.425 position:10% line:83% align:start
How could you figure that out
on the first try?

00:11:31.992 --> 00:11:33.494 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
She's got a point.

00:11:33.628 --> 00:11:35.863 position:7% line:89% align:start
Saionji's scarily good at this.

00:11:36.565 --> 00:11:39.400 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Okay, so right now, you're</i>
 <i>in front of Classroom 1-M,</i>

00:11:39.534 --> 00:11:41.735 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>which means we can rule out</i>
 <i>the second floor,</i>

00:11:41.869 --> 00:11:43.605 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>and logically the first one too.</i>

00:11:43.737 --> 00:11:45.206 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Huh? Why the first floor?

00:11:45.339 --> 00:11:46.473 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's a bad move.

00:11:46.608 --> 00:11:47.808 position:7% line:89% align:start
If she was on the first floor,

00:11:47.942 --> 00:11:49.410 position:24% line:83% align:start
you could find her
with one question.

00:11:49.544 --> 00:11:51.879 position:10% line:83% align:start
The Little Devil's not going
to take a risk like that,

00:11:52.012 --> 00:11:54.281 position:24% line:83% align:start
so we can eliminate
the fourth floor too.

00:11:54.415 --> 00:11:56.317 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Ah, I see,
'cause you're there, right?

00:11:56.450 --> 00:11:58.018 position:21% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] <i>You've seen</i>
 <i>how meticulous she is</i>

00:11:58.152 --> 00:11:59.486 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>when it comes to details.</i>

00:11:59.621 --> 00:12:00.788 position:19% line:89% align:start
No doubt she considered

00:12:00.921 --> 00:12:02.189 position:16% line:83% align:start
that if she moved Himeji
to this floor,

00:12:02.323 --> 00:12:04.491 position:27% line:83% align:start
I would hear it,
and pass the info on to you.

00:12:04.626 --> 00:12:06.293 position:33% line:89% align:start
In that case,

00:12:06.427 --> 00:12:08.663 position:7% line:83% align:start
we can discount the third floor
and the left side of the fifth.

00:12:08.796 --> 00:12:10.197 position:33% line:89% align:start
Huh. Correct.

00:12:10.331 --> 00:12:12.833 position:24% line:83% align:start
The right-hand side
of the third floor is above you,

00:12:12.967 --> 00:12:14.435 position:7% line:89% align:start
while the left side's below me,

00:12:14.569 --> 00:12:16.337 position:13% line:83% align:start
and I've got the left side
of the fifth floor

00:12:16.470 --> 00:12:17.505 position:30% line:89% align:start
just overhead.

00:12:17.938 --> 00:12:19.206 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
All right.

00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:20.474 position:16% line:83% align:start
So with the spaces still
on the fifth floor,

00:12:20.609 --> 00:12:21.475 position:21% line:89% align:start
and all of the sixth.

00:12:21.610 --> 00:12:22.910 position:33% line:89% align:start
Twelve left.

00:12:23.043 --> 00:12:24.745 position:13% line:83% align:start
Nope. We can narrow it down
even further.

00:12:24.878 --> 00:12:25.879 position:16% line:89% align:start
In a game like this one,

00:12:26.013 --> 00:12:27.214 position:7% line:89% align:start
it's good strategy to make sure

00:12:27.348 --> 00:12:28.949 position:30% line:83% align:start
your opponent's
always one space shy

00:12:29.083 --> 00:12:30.384 position:24% line:89% align:start
of their objective.

00:12:30.518 --> 00:12:32.820 position:10% line:83% align:start
Meaning, she's likely hidden
in a classroom

00:12:32.953 --> 00:12:35.222 position:10% line:83% align:start
that's three plus one spaces
away from you.

00:12:35.356 --> 00:12:37.525 position:30% line:83% align:start
The music room
on the fifth floor is too close,

00:12:37.659 --> 00:12:38.627 position:30% line:89% align:start
so that's out.

00:12:38.759 --> 00:12:40.327 position:7% line:89% align:start
Leaving us with three choices.

00:12:41.630 --> 00:12:44.064 position:16% line:83% align:start
A magician never reveals
his secrets, you know?

00:12:44.566 --> 00:12:46.534 position:10% line:83% align:start
-[NOA] Fine, then. Whatever.
-Huh?

00:12:47.001 --> 00:12:49.036 position:19% line:83% align:start
If the logical approach
doesn't work against you,

00:12:49.169 --> 00:12:51.573 position:24% line:83% align:start
then I'll just make
the last hiding spot random.

00:12:51.706 --> 00:12:53.040 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
What? Random?

00:12:53.173 --> 00:12:55.075 position:33% line:83% align:start
Don't tell me
you've gotten that desperate?

00:12:55.510 --> 00:12:58.379 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Oh, that's not it at all.
-[horn blares]

00:12:58.513 --> 00:13:02.283 position:10% line:83% align:start
Don't confuse designed mayhem
for a desperate mess, Hiroto.

00:13:03.250 --> 00:13:05.754 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] That's when Akizuki
took her fourth turn.

00:13:05.919 --> 00:13:07.321 position:21% line:89% align:start
Asking two questions,

00:13:07.454 --> 00:13:09.356 position:16% line:83% align:start
she was able to work out
that Saionji's new hiding spot

00:13:09.490 --> 00:13:11.225 position:33% line:83% align:start
was somewhere
on the second floor.

00:13:11.358 --> 00:13:12.793 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[phone pings]
-[horn blares]

00:13:12.926 --> 00:13:15.462 position:19% line:83% align:start
Talk about a disaster.
Randomness.

00:13:15.597 --> 00:13:17.632 position:21% line:83% align:start
It completely strikes
tactical interplay

00:13:17.766 --> 00:13:18.932 position:24% line:89% align:start
from the equation.

00:13:19.066 --> 00:13:20.535 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Yeah.</i>

00:13:20.669 --> 00:13:21.736 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>That was honestly</i>
 <i>the most detrimental move</i>

00:13:21.869 --> 00:13:22.836 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>she could have made.</i>

00:13:23.304 --> 00:13:24.639 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Hey, Shinohara.

00:13:24.773 --> 00:13:26.106 position:24% line:89% align:start
Is it still doable?

00:13:26.240 --> 00:13:27.808 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Is what "still doable"?</i>

00:13:27.941 --> 00:13:30.779 position:7% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] Like, is there really
any way you can still find Yuki?

00:13:30.911 --> 00:13:32.681 position:41% line:83% align:start
Gotcha,
that's what you were getting at.

00:13:32.813 --> 00:13:34.014 position:21% line:89% align:start
Don't worry about it,

00:13:34.148 --> 00:13:35.784 position:7% line:83% align:start
I've already got a backup plan
lined up.

00:13:35.916 --> 00:13:37.552 position:24% line:89% align:start
Huh? A backup plan?

00:13:37.686 --> 00:13:40.287 position:10% line:83% align:start
You mean you've seriously got
a way to find Yuki?

00:13:40.421 --> 00:13:42.389 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Yup. It was my third option.</i>

00:13:42.524 --> 00:13:44.592 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>In case the exploits</i>
 <i>and Green Star subversion</i>

00:13:44.726 --> 00:13:45.627 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>came to nothing.</i>

00:13:46.026 --> 00:13:47.261 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Ending the game's no biggie.</i>

00:13:47.394 --> 00:13:49.196 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>I've got that part figured out.</i>

00:13:49.698 --> 00:13:51.065 position:44% line:89% align:start
Oh...

00:13:51.198 --> 00:13:53.000 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Honestly, it's what comes after</i>

00:13:53.133 --> 00:13:54.435 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>that still has me thinking.</i>

00:13:54.569 --> 00:13:55.737 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>Like,</i>
 <i>what's the best "win" state</i>

00:13:55.869 --> 00:13:57.739 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>for a situation like thi--</i>

00:13:57.871 --> 00:13:59.073 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Huh? What?</i>

00:13:59.206 --> 00:14:00.775 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm just a little surprised
is all.

00:14:00.908 --> 00:14:03.344 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's hard to believe you've
already thought something up.

00:14:03.477 --> 00:14:05.045 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Don't be too impressed,</i>

00:14:05.179 --> 00:14:06.480 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>there's still room</i>
 <i>for things to go wrong.</i>

00:14:06.614 --> 00:14:07.915 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Take, for instance,</i>

00:14:08.048 --> 00:14:09.617 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>Akizuki's list</i>
 <i>of known abilities.</i>

00:14:09.751 --> 00:14:10.819 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
We only know two.

00:14:10.951 --> 00:14:12.953 position:7% line:89% align:start
Double Action and Area Barrier.

00:14:13.087 --> 00:14:14.388 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Hey, Saionji,</i>

00:14:14.522 --> 00:14:15.790 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>do me a favor</i>
 <i>and check the time.</i>

00:14:15.923 --> 00:14:16.924 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Huh?

00:14:17.057 --> 00:14:18.926 position:7% line:89% align:start
Looks like it's currently 8:52,

00:14:19.059 --> 00:14:20.227 position:41% line:83% align:start
though
wouldn't it have been quicker

00:14:20.361 --> 00:14:21.862 position:33% line:83% align:start
to check that
on your own Device?

00:14:21.995 --> 00:14:23.897 position:44% line:83% align:start
Yeah,
but I wanted you to see it, too.

00:14:24.031 --> 00:14:25.132 position:19% line:89% align:start
Time will be a factor.

00:14:25.265 --> 00:14:26.634 position:19% line:89% align:start
For the next few turns,

00:14:26.768 --> 00:14:28.335 position:13% line:83% align:start
I intend to stretch things
out as much as I can

00:14:28.469 --> 00:14:30.805 position:19% line:83% align:start
until Akizuki and I use
our second Answer Points

00:14:30.938 --> 00:14:32.072 position:21% line:89% align:start
and the data resets.

00:14:32.206 --> 00:14:33.874 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
And that'll achieve what?

00:14:34.007 --> 00:14:36.076 position:38% line:83% align:start
Actually,
if I can pull that off,

00:14:36.210 --> 00:14:37.378 position:13% line:89% align:start
we should instantly be able

00:14:37.512 --> 00:14:39.346 position:35% line:83% align:start
to find out
where Himeji's hiding.

00:14:39.714 --> 00:14:40.881 position:33% line:89% align:start
[phone pings]

00:14:41.014 --> 00:14:42.182 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
So I carried on,

00:14:42.316 --> 00:14:43.884 position:21% line:89% align:start
dragging things out,

00:14:44.017 --> 00:14:45.620 position:41% line:83% align:start
waiting
until the very last second

00:14:45.754 --> 00:14:46.954 position:27% line:89% align:start
to end my turns.

00:14:47.087 --> 00:14:48.389 position:21% line:89% align:start
When Akizuki was up,

00:14:48.523 --> 00:14:50.958 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'd make small talk
to prolong hers, as well.

00:14:54.696 --> 00:14:58.966 position:30% line:89% align:start
[phone pinging]

00:14:59.099 --> 00:15:00.802 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
We called "check" on each other,

00:15:00.934 --> 00:15:02.236 position:19% line:89% align:start
and by the fifth turn,

00:15:02.369 --> 00:15:03.971 position:24% line:83% align:start
both of us had used
our second "Retreat".

00:15:04.304 --> 00:15:07.141 position:27% line:83% align:start
Now, we each had
one Answer Point left.

00:15:07.274 --> 00:15:09.577 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
[giggles] Nicely done, Hiroto.

00:15:09.711 --> 00:15:11.513 position:30% line:83% align:start
I never thought
that you'd be such a match

00:15:11.646 --> 00:15:12.847 position:21% line:89% align:start
for me on my A-Game.

00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:14.348 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm all giddy,

00:15:14.481 --> 00:15:16.183 position:19% line:83% align:start
we might really be made
for each other after all.

00:15:16.316 --> 00:15:18.051 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's been a while
since I received a compliment

00:15:18.185 --> 00:15:19.788 position:21% line:89% align:start
as insincere as that.

00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:21.723 position:30% line:89% align:start
Huh? I mean it.

00:15:21.856 --> 00:15:23.157 position:7% line:89% align:start
In another time, another place,

00:15:23.290 --> 00:15:25.259 position:19% line:83% align:start
things could have been
so different.

00:15:25.392 --> 00:15:28.462 position:19% line:83% align:start
[laughs] Unfortunately,
in the here and now,

00:15:28.596 --> 00:15:29.764 position:30% line:89% align:start
we're enemies.

00:15:29.898 --> 00:15:32.634 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yeah, but this war of ours
is just about over.

00:15:32.767 --> 00:15:34.168 position:24% line:89% align:start
Really? All right.

00:15:34.301 --> 00:15:36.905 position:21% line:83% align:start
Go ahead and end this
if you can, Mr. Confident.

00:15:37.037 --> 00:15:38.740 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Be careful what you wish for.</i>

00:15:38.873 --> 00:15:40.040 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[NOA] <i>Huh?</i>
-Ah.

00:15:40.174 --> 00:15:41.509 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
 <i>Before this turn is over,</i>

00:15:41.643 --> 00:15:43.444 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'm going to know</i>
 <i>Himeji's location.</i>

00:15:43.578 --> 00:15:45.580 position:21% line:83% align:start
[NOA] <i>[laughs] Yeah,</i>
 <i>that's not going to happen.</i>

00:15:45.713 --> 00:15:48.148 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>You're just relying</i>
 <i>on blind luck at this point.</i>

00:15:48.382 --> 00:15:50.117 position:27% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] <i>[laughs]</i>
 <i>If that's what you think,</i>

00:15:50.250 --> 00:15:51.619 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>then shut up and watch.</i>

00:15:52.921 --> 00:15:55.189 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Please. Notice it.

00:15:56.591 --> 00:15:57.559 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm...

00:15:58.593 --> 00:15:59.460 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:15:59.594 --> 00:16:00.562 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:16:00.695 --> 00:16:01.596 position:47% line:89% align:start
Hm.

00:16:02.229 --> 00:16:03.497 position:30% line:89% align:start
So, that's it.

00:16:03.865 --> 00:16:04.732 position:35% line:89% align:start
Thank you.

00:16:05.232 --> 00:16:06.768 position:30% line:89% align:start
Classroom 3-G.

00:16:06.901 --> 00:16:09.671 position:7% line:83% align:start
That's the place you're hiding
Himeji now, isn't it?

00:16:09.804 --> 00:16:10.939 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:16:11.071 --> 00:16:12.540 position:35% line:83% align:start
By the way,
that isn't a "Question",

00:16:12.674 --> 00:16:15.242 position:19% line:83% align:start
because I already know
the answer is yes.

00:16:15.375 --> 00:16:16.511 position:21% line:89% align:start
And since I'm close,

00:16:16.644 --> 00:16:18.847 position:16% line:83% align:start
I can go and assert that
this turn.

00:16:18.979 --> 00:16:20.380 position:19% line:89% align:start
Going random backfired.

00:16:20.515 --> 00:16:22.983 position:7% line:89% align:start
No way. How did you know that?

00:16:23.116 --> 00:16:24.519 position:30% line:83% align:start
-How could you?
-[HIROTO] Earlier,

00:16:24.652 --> 00:16:26.688 position:27% line:83% align:start
when Himeji and I
briefly passed each other

00:16:26.821 --> 00:16:28.121 position:30% line:89% align:start
in the hallway,

00:16:28.255 --> 00:16:29.824 position:33% line:83% align:start
I also passed
a little message on to her.

00:16:29.958 --> 00:16:32.493 position:27% line:83% align:start
[NOA] A message?
I didn't hear you say anything.

00:16:32.627 --> 00:16:34.228 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Oh, I definitely did.

00:16:34.361 --> 00:16:35.930 position:13% line:83% align:start
I told her it was supposed
to get chilly tonight

00:16:36.063 --> 00:16:37.364 position:33% line:89% align:start
after 10 p.m.

00:16:37.498 --> 00:16:39.366 position:16% line:83% align:start
and to the warm the room
to avoid getting cold.

00:16:39.500 --> 00:16:41.769 position:30% line:83% align:start
"Warm the room
to avoid getting cold"?

00:16:41.903 --> 00:16:42.704 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:16:42.837 --> 00:16:43.872 position:41% line:89% align:start
The AC!

00:16:44.271 --> 00:16:45.707 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yup.

00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:47.474 position:5% line:83% align:start
I basically told her to crank up
the thermostat at ten

00:16:47.609 --> 00:16:49.276 position:7% line:89% align:start
to tip me off to her location.

00:16:49.409 --> 00:16:51.445 position:19% line:83% align:start
[gasps] But, the sound
of the air-conditioning going

00:16:51.579 --> 00:16:53.413 position:10% line:89% align:start
doesn't even carry that far!

00:16:53.948 --> 00:16:55.115 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
No, it doesn't.

00:16:55.249 --> 00:16:56.651 position:16% line:89% align:start
However, in most schools,

00:16:56.784 --> 00:17:00.053 position:5% line:83% align:start
AC use can reliably be monitored
from the staff room.

00:17:00.187 --> 00:17:01.488 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
Wait, you don't mean...

00:17:01.623 --> 00:17:03.758 position:38% line:83% align:start
The place
I've been hiding my partner

00:17:03.892 --> 00:17:05.492 position:13% line:89% align:start
is down in the staff room.

00:17:06.193 --> 00:17:08.195 position:13% line:89% align:start
Looks like it's game over.

00:17:08.328 --> 00:17:09.263 position:33% line:89% align:start
My answer...

00:17:09.797 --> 00:17:13.601 position:7% line:83% align:start
Noa Akizuki's partner, Himeji,
is right here!

00:17:14.268 --> 00:17:16.169 position:33% line:89% align:start
[lock clicks]

00:17:16.838 --> 00:17:18.506 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door sliding]

00:17:18.640 --> 00:17:20.675 position:30% line:89% align:start
[bell ringing]

00:17:23.043 --> 00:17:24.177 position:13% line:89% align:start
I've been waiting for you.

00:17:24.311 --> 00:17:25.312 position:27% line:89% align:start
Welcome, Master.

00:17:25.445 --> 00:17:27.381 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah, sorry to keep you waiting.

00:17:27.515 --> 00:17:28.550 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[Noa chuckles]
-Ah.

00:17:28.683 --> 00:17:31.920 position:7% line:89% align:start
[laughs] <i>Sorry. I win, Hiroto.</i>

00:17:32.052 --> 00:17:32.887 position:44% line:89% align:start
What?

00:17:33.021 --> 00:17:34.354 position:35% line:89% align:start
You heard.

00:17:34.488 --> 00:17:35.657 position:30% line:83% align:start
All this time,
I've just been waiting for you

00:17:35.790 --> 00:17:38.392 position:27% line:83% align:start
to finally use up
your third Answer Point.

00:17:38.826 --> 00:17:40.460 position:35% line:89% align:start
Here goes.

00:17:41.161 --> 00:17:43.163 position:7% line:89% align:start
Alter Fate ability, activated.

00:17:43.297 --> 00:17:46.233 position:10% line:83% align:start
Strike Hiroto's final answer
from history!

00:17:46.366 --> 00:17:48.168 position:16% line:83% align:start
-[Shirayuki, Hiroto gasp]
-[alarm blaring]

00:17:48.302 --> 00:17:49.771 position:33% line:89% align:start
"Alter Fate"?

00:17:49.904 --> 00:17:52.306 position:10% line:83% align:start
Did she just completely erase
my answer?

00:17:52.907 --> 00:17:54.042 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:17:54.174 --> 00:17:55.577 position:27% line:83% align:start
You have no idea
how long I've waited

00:17:55.710 --> 00:17:58.178 position:13% line:83% align:start
to see that miserable look
upon your face.

00:17:58.312 --> 00:17:59.747 position:33% line:89% align:start
[horn blares]

00:17:59.881 --> 00:18:00.782 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Himeji!

00:18:00.915 --> 00:18:02.082 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:18:03.885 --> 00:18:05.118 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:18:06.253 --> 00:18:08.322 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
[snickers] Here I am.

00:18:09.023 --> 00:18:11.458 position:24% line:83% align:start
And now, it's time
to end this game for real.

00:18:11.593 --> 00:18:14.829 position:16% line:83% align:start
Answer. Hiroto's partner
is hiding inside this room.

00:18:14.963 --> 00:18:16.664 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door sliding]

00:18:17.364 --> 00:18:19.466 position:30% line:89% align:start
[bell ringing]

00:18:19.968 --> 00:18:20.935 position:35% line:89% align:start
[snickers]

00:18:21.603 --> 00:18:23.805 position:5% line:89% align:start
So you're Hiroto's partner, huh?

00:18:24.371 --> 00:18:26.306 position:38% line:83% align:start
[giggles]
It's so nice to meet you!

00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:28.042 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:18:28.175 --> 00:18:30.177 position:7% line:83% align:start
You've never seen me dressed up
like this before, have you?

00:18:33.413 --> 00:18:34.849 position:21% line:89% align:start
Wait, you're a girl?

00:18:34.983 --> 00:18:36.183 position:41% line:89% align:start
Bingo.

00:18:36.316 --> 00:18:37.150 position:30% line:83% align:start
You and I have
actually crossed paths

00:18:37.284 --> 00:18:38.485 position:27% line:89% align:start
a bunch of times.

00:18:38.620 --> 00:18:40.187 position:41% line:83% align:start
Though,
if you don't mind me saying,

00:18:40.320 --> 00:18:41.488 position:19% line:89% align:start
I never really took you

00:18:41.623 --> 00:18:42.824 position:27% line:83% align:start
for the reckless,
foaming-at-the-mouth

00:18:42.957 --> 00:18:43.825 position:33% line:89% align:start
revenge type.

00:18:43.958 --> 00:18:44.859 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
Why you...

00:18:44.993 --> 00:18:46.094 position:33% line:89% align:start
[grunts] Huh?

00:18:46.828 --> 00:18:49.496 position:30% line:83% align:start
So, is my face
ringing any bells now?

00:18:49.631 --> 00:18:52.033 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
The Empress, Sarasa Saionji?

00:18:52.165 --> 00:18:54.035 position:21% line:89% align:start
But why are you here?

00:18:54.167 --> 00:18:55.737 position:33% line:83% align:start
Let's call it
academic curiosity.

00:18:55.870 --> 00:18:59.239 position:7% line:83% align:start
This sounded fun, so I figured
I should have a look-see.

00:18:59.373 --> 00:19:00.975 position:10% line:89% align:start
But I needn't have bothered.

00:19:01.109 --> 00:19:02.242 position:5% line:89% align:start
Turns out that you were too weak

00:19:02.376 --> 00:19:04.144 position:19% line:83% align:start
to beat that smug jerk
after all.

00:19:04.277 --> 00:19:05.546 position:21% line:89% align:start
What are you saying?

00:19:05.680 --> 00:19:07.414 position:21% line:83% align:start
Do you have any idea
what just happened here?

00:19:07.548 --> 00:19:08.850 position:10% line:89% align:start
I made a deal with the Devil,

00:19:08.983 --> 00:19:10.652 position:21% line:83% align:start
stole the Green Star,
beat the Seven Star,

00:19:10.785 --> 00:19:12.553 position:21% line:83% align:start
subverted the system
of this institution,

00:19:12.687 --> 00:19:14.388 position:13% line:83% align:start
became the strongest person
on the island,

00:19:14.522 --> 00:19:15.623 position:21% line:89% align:start
and you call me weak?

00:19:15.757 --> 00:19:17.224 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Nobody's denying the fact

00:19:17.357 --> 00:19:19.060 position:33% line:83% align:start
that you won
the Tabletop Treasure Hunt.

00:19:19.192 --> 00:19:20.528 position:13% line:89% align:start
But I think you might want

00:19:20.662 --> 00:19:22.764 position:16% line:83% align:start
to double-check who it is
you actually defeated.

00:19:23.698 --> 00:19:26.299 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
